 -&nbsp;12 Zodiac Animal Signs</div><div class=3D"textSection">People=E2=80=
=99s birth years determine their Chinese zodiac signs. However, things are =
not that easy! There is an animal representing each year, but the =E2=80=9C=
year=E2=80=9D is defined by Chinese lunar calendar, not the Gregorian year =
you are familiar with from Jan. 1st to Dec. 31st.<br><br>The dates of Chine=
se Lunar New Year vary every year, but will fall on a day in January or Feb=
ruary. If you were born on a day during March to December, it won=E2=80=99t=
